03:07.560 --> 03:10.463
- Priest: Who are you?
- I already told you.

03:10.496 --> 03:13.199
I wanted to let Jesus
Christ into my life.

03:13.232 --> 03:16.400
I have a feeling you'll be
meeting Jesus quite soon.

03:16.441 --> 03:19.408
The only question is how
much it'll hurt before you do.

03:19.441 --> 03:22.076
What the fuck kind of priest are you?

03:22.117 --> 03:23.443
Please watch your language.

03:23.484 --> 03:25.481
Fuck you, motherfucker.

03:27.385 --> 03:30.646
[coughs]
There's no call for profanity.

03:31.887 --> 03:34.052
Spend some time with
our confused friend.

03:34.085 --> 03:37.054
See if you can show him the light.

03:41.462 --> 03:44.229
Well, I thought he'd never leave.

03:44.262 --> 03:45.662
[gasps]

03:45.695 --> 03:48.631
See, now, that won't be necessary.

03:48.671 --> 03:50.736
Shut your mouth.

03:55.943 --> 03:57.308
[groans]

04:08.425 --> 04:10.855
[panting]

04:23.837 --> 04:25.500
[grunts]

04:26.870 --> 04:28.773
<i>- Fuck me.
- Man: Down!</i>

04:29.742 --> 04:32.046
Get him! I need him alive!

04:36.345 --> 04:38.008
[grunts]

04:51.424 --> 04:53.557
[panting]

04:59.096 --> 05:01.100
[yells]

05:02.996 --> 05:04.633
Fuck!

05:08.571 --> 05:10.339
Ah!

05:11.541 --> 05:14.577
[Gordon chuckles]
Deva: Like that.

05:14.611 --> 05:16.111
Good morning, everybody.

05:16.144 --> 05:17.678
- Max: Hey, Mom.
- Deva: Hey.

05:17.711 --> 05:21.012
<i>- Hi.
- Deva: That's sick! I love it.</i>

05:22.478 --> 05:24.519
- That's pretty cool.
- How did you sleep?

05:24.552 --> 05:26.183
Good.

05:26.216 --> 05:27.886
<i>- Deva: Do you like it?
- Max: Yeah.</i>

05:27.919 --> 05:30.221
Me, too. It's awesome.

05:30.254 --> 05:32.452
Hey, you know what? Let's
go outside and try it out.

05:32.485 --> 05:35.259
- You gonna do an awesome trick?
- Max: Oh, yeah.

05:35.292 --> 05:38.258
Deva: I think you are.
[Max chuckles]

05:50.565 --> 05:52.438
Carrie: I miss this.

05:53.472 --> 05:55.639
And I missed you.

06:00.879 --> 06:04.113
Do you think we could ever get it back?

06:06.819 --> 06:09.092
I don't know.

06:09.125 --> 06:12.492
Probably not this, but
maybe something different.

06:12.525 --> 06:14.762
Something better?

06:20.237 --> 06:22.773
I'm sorry I lied to you.

06:24.174 --> 06:26.011
I know.

06:26.044 --> 06:29.011
<i>Carrie: Sometimes when you
live with a lie for long enough,</i>

06:29.044 --> 06:31.314
<i>it starts to feel like the truth.</i>

06:31.347 --> 06:33.314
<i>- Hey, Alma.
- Hey.</i>

06:33.347 --> 06:35.449
Proctor arrest. You up for it?

06:35.482 --> 06:37.281
Sure looks like a lot of paperwork.

06:37.313 --> 06:39.012
How much is it gonna cost me?

06:39.045 --> 06:40.546
Are you kidding me?

06:40.579 --> 06:43.447
- It's Proctor. It's on the house.
- Thanks.

06:43.480 --> 06:46.153
<i>Besides, we both know you
would just screw it up.</i>

06:48.659 --> 06:51.093
- Hey, Emmett.
- Sheriff.

06:54.831 --> 06:56.931
<i>- You come for these?
- No.</i>

06:56.964 --> 07:00.298
- I don't deserve that badge.
- Come on.

07:00.331 --> 07:02.402
No one deserves it more than you.

07:02.435 --> 07:04.403
Have you heard back
from the D.A.'s office?

07:04.436 --> 07:06.843
You let me worry about the D.A., okay?

07:06.876 --> 07:09.213
<i>- Listen, what I did to those men...
- They had it coming.</i>

07:09.246 --> 07:11.843
- Not from me.
- Well, if not from you...

07:13.042 --> 07:16.710
Listen, Emmett, there are rules,

07:16.743 --> 07:18.916
- and then there's what's right.
- And then there's God.

07:18.949 --> 07:21.979
Yeah, God kind of takes all
the fun out of the argument.

07:24.220 --> 07:26.418
This job is doing something to me.

07:26.451 --> 07:29.416
I can't risk becoming
the man I was last night.

07:31.457 --> 07:34.687
- So, what are you gonna do?
- My sister lives down in Florida.

07:34.728 --> 07:37.326
I'm gonna head down there for a while.

07:37.359 --> 07:39.262
See what it feels like.

07:44.102 --> 07:46.268
I hate to lose you.

07:47.637 --> 07:49.601
You know, you may have
everyone else fooled,

07:49.634 --> 07:52.105
not me.

07:55.002 --> 07:56.568
How's that?

07:56.609 --> 07:58.639
I know you're a good man.

07:59.976 --> 08:02.111
It's been an honor to work with you.

08:04.543 --> 08:06.710
You, too.

08:29.726 --> 08:32.863
<i>Woman on P.A.: Dr.
Hadman to E.R. bay 13.</i>

08:32.904 --> 08:36.072
<i>Dr. Hadman to E.R. bay 13.</i>

08:38.302 --> 08:41.905
[heart monitor beeping]

08:41.938 --> 08:43.905
Hey, man,

08:43.938 --> 08:46.272
give me some fuckin' morphine.

08:46.305 --> 08:50.210
[wheezes] I'm dyin' here.

08:50.243 --> 08:53.249
I've been ringing this bell
for a fuckin' hour already.

08:53.282 --> 08:56.413
Where the fuck do you people go?

09:01.720 --> 09:03.191
Oh, shit.

09:03.224 --> 09:06.452
<i>- That's right.
- You gotta tell Proctor</i>

09:06.493 --> 09:08.018
I didn't tell them anything.

09:08.059 --> 09:10.119
By the time they came to me,

09:10.152 --> 09:11.591
they knew all about it.

09:11.624 --> 09:15.927
What the fuck are you doing?
That's my fuckin' morphine drip!

09:15.960 --> 09:19.463
[wheezing]
You won't be needing that anymore.

09:19.528 --> 09:20.767
[wheezing continues]

09:20.800 --> 09:24.503
You were paid to transport
Mr. Proctor's merchandise

09:24.536 --> 09:26.606
and keep your mouth shut.

09:26.639 --> 09:28.902
You chose to speak to the authorities.

09:28.943 --> 09:33.044
As such, Mr. Proctor has
asked me to inform you

09:33.076 --> 09:35.643
<i>that your services will
no longer be required.</i>

09:35.676 --> 09:37.549
Get the fuck away from me...

09:37.582 --> 09:39.684
[groans]

09:39.717 --> 09:42.985
[wheezing]

09:44.114 --> 09:46.416
[gasping]

09:49.519 --> 09:51.484
[gasps]

09:51.517 --> 09:53.755
[monitor hums]

09:56.556 --> 09:59.395
[rapid beeping]

10:11.335 --> 10:15.734
<i>♪ 7:00 and my heartbeat stops ♪</i>

10:15.775 --> 10:18.469
<i>♪ My candy girl ♪</i>

10:20.638 --> 10:22.940
<i>♪ One in a crowd ♪</i>

10:22.973 --> 10:27.643
<i>♪ Can she shout and still be heard? ♪</i>

10:29.451 --> 10:33.649
<i>♪ 7:00 and my heartbeat stops ♪</i>

10:33.682 --> 10:36.886
<i>♪ My candy girl ♪</i>

10:38.888 --> 10:41.592
<i>♪ One in a crowd ♪</i>

10:41.625 --> 10:46.231
<i>♪ Can she shout and still be heard? ♪</i>

10:47.864 --> 10:52.130
<i>♪ But I'm still here ♪</i>

10:52.163 --> 10:56.561
<i>♪ My candy girl ♪</i>

11:05.175 --> 11:06.436
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

11:06.469 --> 11:10.940
<i>♪ Grey and endless ♪</i>

11:10.973 --> 11:15.578
<i>♪ Grey and endless ♪</i>

11:15.611 --> 11:20.018
<i>♪ Grey and endless ♪</i>

11:20.051 --> 11:25.018
<i>♪ Grey and endless ♪</i>

11:33.359 --> 11:36.997
<i>♪ 11:00... ♪</i>

11:48.468 --> 11:50.633
What are you doing here, Sugar?

11:50.673 --> 11:53.038
You came to see me when I was inside.

11:53.070 --> 11:55.468
I'm just returning the favor.

11:55.501 --> 11:58.138
<i>Seeing if there's anything you need.</i>

11:59.003 --> 12:01.306
Yeah?

12:05.814 --> 12:07.252
And where was your friendship

12:07.285 --> 12:09.851
while Hood was making his plans?

12:09.884 --> 12:12.249
A simple warning is
all I would have needed.

12:12.282 --> 12:15.288
Hood, he doesn't consult with me.

12:15.321 --> 12:17.023
Yeah?

12:17.056 --> 12:19.426
Would you have told me if he had?

12:23.024 --> 12:25.757
Kai...

12:25.798 --> 12:28.164
I've known you since you were a kid.

12:28.197 --> 12:30.099
We may not be friends,

12:30.132 --> 12:33.204
but in some way, we're still family.

12:35.669 --> 12:38.675
We're not family. Not anymore.

12:39.571 --> 12:42.304
You made your choice.

12:42.337 --> 12:45.109
And don't come back.

12:47.173 --> 12:49.739
Kai, it doesn't have to be this way.

12:51.877 --> 12:53.949
Yes, it does.

12:53.982 --> 12:56.716
<i>I forgave what I could, given
the years you lost for me.</i>

12:56.749 --> 12:59.386
But when I get out of here...
and I will get out of here...

12:59.419 --> 13:01.721
I'll be coming for Hood.

13:01.754 --> 13:04.292
And if you're standing
between us, I'll cut you down

13:04.325 --> 13:06.431
without a second thought.

13:10.135 --> 13:11.766
[knocks]

13:12.767 --> 13:15.132
You shouldn't have come here.

13:24.504 --> 13:28.309
Hey, boss, we might have a
glitch with Proctor's case.

13:28.342 --> 13:31.077
Just get your son and go.
You can't ever come back here.

13:31.110 --> 13:33.677
Why are you helping me?

13:33.710 --> 13:36.813
I know what it feels like to
be trapped in your own life.

13:36.854 --> 13:38.548
<i>Siobhan: I went to check on Juliet.</i>

13:38.581 --> 13:41.187
She missed her shift at the Savoy.

13:41.220 --> 13:44.355
<i>- Juliet: And what about you?
- I made my choice.</i>

13:44.420 --> 13:46.860
<i>- Juliet: Thank you.
- Just go.</i>

13:47.757 --> 13:49.397
<i>Siobhan: I swung by the day care center.</i>

13:49.430 --> 13:51.431
<i>Apparently, she pulled her son
out in the middle of the day.</i>

13:51.464 --> 13:53.734
<i>The director there had a
feeling she's not coming back.</i>

13:53.767 --> 13:55.469
Smart girl.

13:55.502 --> 13:58.868
<i>- What about your case against Proctor?
- She was never gonna testify.</i>

14:00.276 --> 14:02.971
<i>Anyway, we've got a stronger
case with Longshadow.</i>

14:09.283 --> 14:10.882
Hi.

14:10.915 --> 14:12.650
<i>Lucas: He has a list of
people Proctor extorted</i>

14:12.683 --> 14:14.818
<i>to clear the land for the new casino.</i>

14:14.851 --> 14:17.089
And you think Longshadow's
gonna see that through?

14:17.120 --> 14:19.180
He wants Proctor out
of his hair for good.

14:19.221 --> 14:21.852
The charges against my
uncle will soon be dropped.

14:21.885 --> 14:24.421
You've nothing to worry about.

14:24.454 --> 14:27.558
But I am worried, Rebecca.

14:27.591 --> 14:29.463
I don't doubt for a
moment Proctor's lawyers

14:29.496 --> 14:32.164
will buy his way out
of a few gun charges.

14:32.197 --> 14:34.396
But the cops have papers
linking him to the Kinaho Moon

14:34.429 --> 14:36.267
and I can't have that.

14:36.300 --> 14:38.570
That sounds like something

14:38.603 --> 14:41.002
you should talk to him
about when he gets out.

14:41.035 --> 14:43.473
<i>- Siobhan: Why now?
- What?</i>

14:43.506 --> 14:45.505
Proctor...  why now?

14:45.538 --> 14:47.501
That's why I'm here, isn't it?

14:47.542 --> 14:49.138
<i>I don't know why you're here.</i>

14:49.171 --> 14:50.802
I've been trying to pinpoint in my mind

14:50.843 --> 14:52.939
what it is about you...
procedure, protocols, laws...

14:52.972 --> 14:54.876
you just don't have
patience for any of it.

14:55.782 --> 14:57.318
Rebecca,

14:57.351 --> 14:59.812
your uncle has had a long run,

14:59.853 --> 15:02.513
but his luck's about to run out.

15:02.554 --> 15:04.681
I don't think that they're
gonna take him down for this,

15:04.722 --> 15:07.523
I know it, because I'm
gonna help them do it.

15:07.556 --> 15:09.757
Why are you telling me this?

15:11.927 --> 15:15.033
It's time for you to make a choice.

15:18.806 --> 15:21.235
Why me?

15:23.107 --> 15:24.770
I like you.

15:24.803 --> 15:27.305
[chuckles]

15:53.973 --> 15:56.509
The warrant is specific to the basement

15:56.574 --> 15:58.941
and excludes any and all
other rooms of the house.

15:58.974 --> 16:01.844
So, it could be argued
that the subbasement

16:01.877 --> 16:03.884
in which the contraband was found

16:03.917 --> 16:06.852
wasn't on the warrant and
is, therefore, inadmissible.

16:06.885 --> 16:09.020
- Would that work?
- 50/50.

16:09.053 --> 16:10.724
Depends on the judge.

16:10.757 --> 16:12.860
Meanwhile, I'm pushing
for a new bail hearing.

16:12.893 --> 16:15.356
The A.D.A. is arguing flight risk.

16:15.397 --> 16:18.228
But all the new ones do that,
so I will push it through.

16:18.261 --> 16:20.164
It'll just take a day or two.

16:20.197 --> 16:23.364
- What about Longshadow?
- Well, that's a whole 'nother ball of wax.

16:23.404 --> 16:27.066
- You sure he's gonna go through with it?
- Rebecca: He seemed very sure.

16:27.107 --> 16:30.000
Yeah. Well, we'll have
to see what he's got.

16:30.041 --> 16:32.737
<i>Until then, my number one
priority is to get you out of here.</i>

16:32.778 --> 16:35.611
So I will call you as soon
as I have anything new.

16:35.644 --> 16:38.450
- Thank you.
- Rebecca, I will wait for you outside.

16:45.491 --> 16:47.487
What is it?

16:48.622 --> 16:50.514
It never rains, but it pours.

16:50.555 --> 16:51.954
You're worried about Alex?

16:51.987 --> 16:55.956
Well, he picked a hell of
a time to grow some balls.

16:57.357 --> 17:00.292
Well, can't Sperling
do anything about that?

17:00.333 --> 17:01.468
Maybe.

17:02.395 --> 17:04.193
Maybe.

17:04.266 --> 17:05.724
Uncle?

17:07.493 --> 17:11.195
Just go home, Rebecca.
I'll talk to you tomorrow.

17:11.237 --> 17:13.435
Okay.

17:19.538 --> 17:21.809
<i>[pounds]
[door opens]</i>

17:23.242 --> 17:25.346
You've got another visitor.

17:39.453 --> 17:41.021
Mother.

17:41.054 --> 17:43.155
Hello, Kai.

17:58.032 --> 18:00.131
You look tired.

18:02.265 --> 18:04.633
I'm not tired.

18:04.667 --> 18:06.370
Just older.

18:10.840 --> 18:12.837
Why are you here?

18:12.870 --> 18:15.508
A mother hears her son is alone

18:15.541 --> 18:17.644
and in trouble.

18:19.141 --> 18:21.676
Well...

18:21.717 --> 18:25.113
I've been alone for
many years, Mother...

18:25.146 --> 18:28.076
for my entire adult life.

18:30.748 --> 18:32.915
As have I.

18:35.717 --> 18:38.219
Does my father know you're here?

18:39.818 --> 18:42.151
Your father demands contrition

18:42.192 --> 18:45.022
from everyone except himself.

18:47.696 --> 18:50.064
As I get older,

18:50.097 --> 18:53.336
I have far less patience for arrogance

18:53.369 --> 18:55.565
disguised as righteousness.

18:56.765 --> 19:00.466
- And yet you stay.
- And yet I stay.

19:02.739 --> 19:05.601
I was not raised to think
there was another way.

19:07.577 --> 19:09.912
By the time I came to it on my own,

19:09.945 --> 19:11.973
I was an old lady.

19:19.517 --> 19:21.948
I failed you, Kai.

19:21.981 --> 19:25.953
I let the dogma of small-minded men

19:25.986 --> 19:27.448
determine your fate

19:27.489 --> 19:30.485
when I should have
been protecting you...

19:30.518 --> 19:33.590
the way any other mother in the world

19:33.623 --> 19:35.421
<i>would have protected her young.</i>

19:35.454 --> 19:39.492
<i>And now I see you in here, and I know</i>

19:39.525 --> 19:42.393
<i>that we put you here...</i>

19:42.426 --> 19:44.559
your father and I.

19:52.470 --> 19:56.433
Your crimes, whatever they may be,

19:56.466 --> 19:59.231
are my crimes.

20:02.672 --> 20:04.872
[sobs softly]

20:16.577 --> 20:18.947
May I come see you again?

20:25.555 --> 20:27.688
Yeah.

20:30.456 --> 20:33.494
<i>[door slides open]</i>

20:37.097 --> 20:39.167
<i>[slides shut]</i>

20:39.200 --> 20:41.334
<i>[distant siren wailing]</i>

20:51.977 --> 20:54.949
<i>[door opens]
Can I help you?</i>

20:54.982 --> 20:59.115
Captain Julias Bonner, NYPD.

20:59.148 --> 21:01.083
<i>So you are not here to pray?</i>

21:01.116 --> 21:02.755
No.

21:02.821 --> 21:04.788
Just doing a little legwork for the FBI.

21:04.821 --> 21:09.690
- Priest: Where is Agent Racine?
- They don't seem to know.

21:09.723 --> 21:12.458
Maybe that's why they
asked me to drop by...

21:12.491 --> 21:14.559
to see if maybe you knew.

21:14.592 --> 21:17.432
I haven't seen Agent Racine in a while.

21:17.465 --> 21:20.000
He was not a healthy man.

21:20.033 --> 21:23.136
<i>Bonner: But he did come
in here from time to time.</i>

21:23.169 --> 21:26.237
Yes. He was looking for my brother.

21:26.270 --> 21:28.601
I take it you haven't
heard from him, either.

21:28.635 --> 21:30.633
If I had, do you think I would tell you?

21:30.674 --> 21:33.408
No, I guess you wouldn't.

21:33.441 --> 21:36.177
I don't suppose you'd allow
me to search the place.

21:36.210 --> 21:40.081
Yes, of course, as soon as
you show me your warrant.

21:40.114 --> 21:43.587
Why all this interest? Surely
you have more pressing cases.

21:43.620 --> 21:45.452
[chuckles] Oh, yes.

21:45.485 --> 21:48.122
But you never seem to
forget the one that got away.

21:48.187 --> 21:50.519
I almost nailed him a long time ago.

21:50.553 --> 21:53.926
I picked up this kid
doing a job for him.

21:53.991 --> 21:55.389
Diamonds.

21:57.296 --> 21:58.728
It's for you.

21:58.761 --> 22:01.965
Turns out it was Rabbit
who tipped us off.

22:01.998 --> 22:06.665
<i>I tried to turn the kid, but he was,</i>

22:06.698 --> 22:09.634
you know, committed.

22:09.667 --> 22:13.507
Everyone must live or
die by their own code.

22:13.540 --> 22:16.544
Of course.

22:16.577 --> 22:20.975
[chuckles] Well, you
have a good day, Father.

22:21.008 --> 22:23.584
Have a good day.

22:24.754 --> 22:26.522
<i>Rabbit: They're closing in...</i>

22:26.555 --> 22:30.184
the intruder last night, now this cop.

22:30.225 --> 22:32.359
They will be here soon.

22:32.392 --> 22:35.823
I had hoped to be a bit stronger

22:35.856 --> 22:37.897
when I faced them.

22:37.930 --> 22:41.297
<i>[heart monitor beeping]</i>

22:44.672 --> 22:47.532
<i>Priest: It was a mistake
sending the assassin after them.</i>

22:47.565 --> 22:49.467
We should have waited
until you were healthy.

22:49.500 --> 22:52.306
The only mistake was her failure.

22:52.339 --> 22:53.675
You could not have foreseen that.

22:53.708 --> 22:56.910
<i>[beeping accelerates]</i>

22:59.949 --> 23:02.050
<i>[rapid beeping]</i>

23:02.083 --> 23:03.577
[yelps]

23:03.618 --> 23:05.552
- Who the fuck are you?
- I'm a nurse, man.

23:05.585 --> 23:07.614
<i>Rabbit: What about this intruder?</i>

23:07.647 --> 23:10.784
He proved more resourceful
than we imagined.

23:10.825 --> 23:13.789
There are only so many hospitals
in the city. We will find him.

23:13.822 --> 23:15.523
- Job: Which one?
- New York Presbyterian.

23:15.556 --> 23:19.288
- Was I shot?
- No, dude. You got hit by a car.

23:19.321 --> 23:21.289
Rabbit: We have to assume
he will get word to them.

23:21.322 --> 23:24.298
<i>He was badly hurt. He may
not get word to anyone.</i>

23:24.331 --> 23:27.603
- How long have I been here?
- I don't know. My shift started at noon.

23:27.636 --> 23:29.033
- Are the cops here?
- Why would the cops be here?

23:29.066 --> 23:30.895
<i>Priest: I have called everyone in.</i>

23:30.936 --> 23:32.904
We will be ready for them.

23:32.937 --> 23:34.801
What the hell are you doing?
No, you can't get out of bed.

23:34.842 --> 23:36.873
- Tell me where my fucking clothes are.
- You can't go anywhere.

23:36.906 --> 23:39.744
- They're gonna fucking kill me, man.
- No one's gonna kill you.

23:39.777 --> 23:42.480
- They're gonna fucking kill me.
- You have a serious concussion. You can't go anywhere.

23:42.513 --> 23:44.248
- The fuck I can't.
- Please just get back in the bed!

23:44.281 --> 23:46.751
- I need some help in here!
- Get the fuck off me!

23:46.784 --> 23:48.150
[panting]

23:48.183 --> 23:50.685
Hey, sorry to keep you waiting.

23:50.718 --> 23:52.716
It's all right. I just got here.

23:52.749 --> 23:55.115
Hey, Laura, can I get a cup of coffee?

23:57.851 --> 24:00.089
A few days ago, that building blew up.

24:00.122 --> 24:02.457
Word is it was an ecstasy lab.

24:02.490 --> 24:04.024
Proctor?

24:04.057 --> 24:07.527
Well, not that we can prove, but, yeah.

24:07.560 --> 24:08.895
Thanks.

24:08.928 --> 24:11.167
I've requested a forensics
team from the DEA,

24:11.200 --> 24:13.703
but first they gotta find us on a map.

24:15.335 --> 24:17.301
So I'm guessing this is
not a defective gas line.

24:17.334 --> 24:20.540
Mm-mm, truck went through a wall
and then the place went sky-high.

24:23.972 --> 24:25.906
Is that it? I mean, why
are you showing me this?

24:25.939 --> 24:27.505
Because the day before this happened,

24:27.546 --> 24:29.943
I was out there with Hood and
Emmett. We shook down some guys.

24:29.976 --> 24:31.774
We found out this is where
they're making the drugs.

24:31.807 --> 24:33.813
<i>And Hood desperately
wanted to tie it to Proctor,</i>

24:33.846 --> 24:36.679
<i>- but we couldn't.
- And then it blows up.</i>

24:37.648 --> 24:39.015
Just like that.

24:39.055 --> 24:40.420
And then he busts Proctor on a warrant

24:40.453 --> 24:42.850
based on information from
a confidential informant.

24:42.883 --> 24:46.184
Exactly. And I wouldn't bet
the farm on that warrant.

24:46.217 --> 24:48.353
Shit.

24:50.396 --> 24:52.733
What the hell is he up to?

24:59.930 --> 25:02.336
George.

25:02.369 --> 25:04.872
Long day?

25:04.905 --> 25:06.903
The only kind I seem
to be having these days.

25:06.936 --> 25:08.039
Drink?

25:08.072 --> 25:09.710
No.

25:11.807 --> 25:14.646
That was some stunt you
pulled with the council.

25:14.679 --> 25:18.080
Oh, George, don't be a sore loser.

25:19.090 --> 25:20.689
Men voted their consciences.

25:22.225 --> 25:23.487
Well, I'm sure you've heard

25:23.520 --> 25:25.255
that your good friend Proctor

25:25.288 --> 25:27.826
has once again been incarcerated.

25:28.828 --> 25:31.668
Proctor's no friend of mine.

25:31.701 --> 25:33.203
As a matter of fact, I'm taking measures

25:33.237 --> 25:35.506
to make sure he goes down for the count.

25:37.938 --> 25:40.872
Maybe I underestimated you.

25:42.873 --> 25:47.052
But maybe you underestimated me, too.

25:52.954 --> 25:55.288
This dagger

25:55.321 --> 25:58.491
belonged to my great-grandfather.

25:58.525 --> 26:00.597
It's handed down as a totem

26:00.630 --> 26:04.070
to the first-born
male of each generation

26:04.103 --> 26:06.237
when he comes of age.

26:06.270 --> 26:08.970
<i>So far, every man in my family</i>

26:09.003 --> 26:11.074
who has carried this knife

26:11.107 --> 26:13.244
has had occasion to use it.

26:13.277 --> 26:16.952
Of course, I have no sons.

26:21.949 --> 26:25.126
Is this your occasion, George?

26:25.159 --> 26:27.497
Is that why you're here?

26:33.338 --> 26:35.868
I didn't think so.

26:36.795 --> 26:38.162
[sighs]

26:41.340 --> 26:43.646
<i>[thumps]
[gasps]</i>

26:43.679 --> 26:47.479
<i>[footsteps receding]
[door opens]</i>

26:57.021 --> 27:00.463
<i>Carrie: It's hard to
know when I realized it.</i>

27:00.496 --> 27:03.494
Little girls love their fathers.

27:03.527 --> 27:06.101
And mine was so loving,

27:06.134 --> 27:08.333
so attentive.

27:08.366 --> 27:10.134
And he kept me in this little world,

27:10.167 --> 27:14.513
and I had no other
reality to compare it to.

27:17.680 --> 27:19.111
So what changed?

27:19.144 --> 27:21.247
Kids in school.

27:22.551 --> 27:24.686
They started to tease me.

27:24.719 --> 27:27.184
And you know how kids can be.

27:29.959 --> 27:33.059
Then this one day, I was
walking home from school

27:33.092 --> 27:35.154
and I passed by a newsstand.

27:37.291 --> 27:40.993
And my father's picture was on
the front page of every paper.

27:42.064 --> 27:44.461
<i>So I bought a copy and I read it.</i>

27:44.494 --> 27:46.658
And I didn't understand
much... I was about 11,

27:46.691 --> 27:48.466
but I understood enough.

27:49.996 --> 27:53.236
They were saying that my
father had had people killed.

27:54.805 --> 27:57.205
So I took the paper and
I put it on his pillow...

27:58.078 --> 28:00.242
and I went to sleep.

28:00.275 --> 28:02.471
And then the next morning,
he was sitting in my room

28:02.504 --> 28:05.143
in an old rocking chair
I had in the corner,

28:05.176 --> 28:09.279
just rocking back and
forth, staring at me.

28:09.312 --> 28:12.048
And for the first time in
my life, I was scared of him.

28:12.081 --> 28:14.320
<i>Jesus, Carrie.</i>

28:18.251 --> 28:21.120
But then he picked me up...

28:21.153 --> 28:24.153
put me in his lap, and
I was barely awake...

28:27.530 --> 28:29.161
kissed me on my head,

28:29.194 --> 28:31.297
and just rocked me back and forth

28:31.330 --> 28:33.925
<i>and I almost fell asleep again.</i>

28:39.565 --> 28:41.869
He was my daddy.

28:42.774 --> 28:44.541
Hey...

28:46.479 --> 28:47.975
that's enough.

28:48.016 --> 28:50.610
You'll have plenty of time
to tell me the rest of it.

28:52.274 --> 28:55.578
- Yeah, I should get going.
- No, no, no. Shh.

28:56.620 --> 28:58.251
No.

28:59.453 --> 29:01.557
No, you shouldn't.

29:11.432 --> 29:13.303
You okay?

29:15.208 --> 29:18.769
Yeah. I'm just thinking about Emmett.

29:20.003 --> 29:21.410
<i>Yeah.</i>

29:21.443 --> 29:24.380
I just can't believe
he lost it like that.

29:28.052 --> 29:29.946
Well, I don't think he did lose it.

29:29.979 --> 29:32.354
I think he made a conscious choice.

29:33.388 --> 29:35.987
They hurt his family,

29:36.020 --> 29:38.796
- he needed to make 'em pay.
- We would have made them pay.

29:38.861 --> 29:40.893
Yeah, but he needed it to come from him.

29:40.926 --> 29:43.165
Think of it like you and Breece.

29:43.198 --> 29:45.994
<i>Look, there is a point at which</i>

29:46.035 --> 29:48.435
<i>any one of us will do
exactly what Emmett did.</i>

29:48.468 --> 29:51.205
It's just a question of what
puts us in that situation

29:51.238 --> 29:55.278
where the circumstances
outweigh the consequences.

29:55.311 --> 29:58.643
We go to the Cadi every day and we're
supposed to be dealing in justice,

29:58.676 --> 30:01.082
but...

30:01.115 --> 30:03.715
all we're really doing is
enforcing a set of rules.

30:04.788 --> 30:08.523
<i>But justice... real justice...</i>

30:08.556 --> 30:10.788
is personal.

30:12.262 --> 30:13.925
Sometimes the only way to get it

30:13.966 --> 30:15.460
is with your own two hands.

30:15.501 --> 30:19.467
You scare the shit out of me
when you say things like that.

30:19.500 --> 30:21.499
You're the one that
wanted me to talk more.

30:21.532 --> 30:24.669
[cell phone ringing]
Yeah, I'm starting to have second thoughts.

30:28.875 --> 30:31.474
[Siobhan giggles]

30:31.515 --> 30:34.751
You're the only sheriff that
doesn't answer his phone.

30:36.289 --> 30:38.225
<i>[ringing continues]</i>

30:38.258 --> 30:41.327
- What?
- You need to get your ass to New York now.

30:41.360 --> 30:43.126
Job?

30:43.159 --> 30:44.894
<i>I'm in deep shit here, man.</i>

30:44.927 --> 30:46.830
Whoa, slow down, slow
down. Where are you?

30:46.863 --> 30:48.264
In the hospital is where I am.

30:48.297 --> 30:50.369
New York Presbyterian, room 307.

30:50.402 --> 30:53.041
<i>- And if Rabbit get here first, I'll be...
- You found him?</i>

30:53.906 --> 30:55.504
Yeah, I found him.

30:57.242 --> 31:01.283
- Now he gonna find me.
- I'm on my way.

31:01.316 --> 31:04.355
- What? What's wrong?
- I have to go.

31:04.388 --> 31:06.219
What, just like that?

31:06.252 --> 31:09.092
You don't think I'm entitled to
more of an explanation than that?

31:09.125 --> 31:12.793
Yeah, you are, but right
now I just don't have time.

31:12.826 --> 31:14.858
Well, are you coming back?

31:14.899 --> 31:17.762
- Not tonight.
- How about ever?

31:20.570 --> 31:22.433
I don't know.

31:22.466 --> 31:25.868
- Then don't go.
- I have to.

31:25.901 --> 31:28.332
[sighs]

31:28.373 --> 31:29.974
I don't think I can do this anymore.

31:30.007 --> 31:33.048
I mean, I don't even know who you are.

31:36.081 --> 31:37.750
I know.

31:40.783 --> 31:43.120
I'm sorry.

31:46.928 --> 31:48.423
<i>[door closes]</i>

32:00.075 --> 32:02.108
Hello, Brock.
[coughs]

32:02.149 --> 32:04.582
Shit. Sorry about that.

32:04.615 --> 32:07.380
- It's fine.
- Wasn't expecting anyone, clearly.

32:07.421 --> 32:08.817
Don't worry about it.

32:08.850 --> 32:11.550
What the hell are you doing
here? I got the night shift.

32:11.583 --> 32:13.085
I have to leave town tonight.

32:13.118 --> 32:14.950
- Where are you going?
- It's not important.

32:14.983 --> 32:16.856
- For how long?
- I don't know.

32:16.889 --> 32:18.730
[sighs]

32:21.366 --> 32:22.899
You're in charge.

32:22.932 --> 32:25.233
Yeah, because that worked
out so well last time.

32:29.366 --> 32:31.599
Hood.

32:34.410 --> 32:36.276
Who the hell are you?

32:39.981 --> 32:43.114
You're a good man, Brock. Take care.

32:59.325 --> 33:01.299
[gasping]

33:11.600 --> 33:13.902
<i>[knocking on door]</i>

33:15.535 --> 33:17.111
Are you expecting anyone?

33:17.144 --> 33:20.410
No. It's okay. I got it.

33:20.451 --> 33:22.481
<i>[knocking]</i>

33:22.514 --> 33:25.077
<i>Are you expecting somebody?</i>

33:33.425 --> 33:35.861
- Hood, what the hell is this?
- Carrie here?

33:35.894 --> 33:37.754
- Are you serious?
- If she's here, I need to see her now.

33:37.787 --> 33:39.887
- Go fuck yourself.
- Gordon, it's okay.

33:39.920 --> 33:42.055
- Yeah, the hell it is.
- What is it?

33:43.097 --> 33:45.931
- What?
- Job found Rabbit.

33:45.965 --> 33:49.141
<i>- Oh, my God. Where?
- New York.</i>

33:49.174 --> 33:50.906
Job's hurt. I'm going now.

33:50.939 --> 33:52.201
- I'm coming.
- What?

33:52.234 --> 33:53.903
- Give us a minute.
- We have to go, now.

33:53.936 --> 33:56.504
Give us a minute. Gordon, honey...

33:56.537 --> 33:58.578
Look, this is your first
night back in this house.

33:58.611 --> 34:00.283
I know, but if Rabbit's in New York...

34:00.316 --> 34:02.653
- None of this shit makes any sense.
- I know it doesn't.

34:02.686 --> 34:05.588
But I have to do this, to
protect us, to protect our family.

34:05.622 --> 34:07.693
- If we're gonna have a chance...
- And how are we gonna have a chance

34:07.726 --> 34:09.820
when he keeps showing up
here? What is it with you?

34:09.860 --> 34:11.260
Why is any of this your problem?

34:11.293 --> 34:13.290
Don't look at her, I'm
the one talking to you.

34:13.322 --> 34:15.701
I don't have time for this shit.
You can stay here if you want.

34:15.734 --> 34:17.230
Hey, stop fucking talking to her.

34:17.271 --> 34:19.869
- Don't you turn your back on me.
- Gordon, stop it!

34:19.902 --> 34:21.972
- Fuck you!
- Jesus Christ!

34:22.005 --> 34:23.666
Now, how many times are
you gonna ruin our lives?

34:23.706 --> 34:26.274
- This has nothing to do with you.
- Gordon, put the gun down.

34:26.308 --> 34:28.476
- You don't understand.
- What, are you protecting him?

34:28.510 --> 34:30.907
- No.
- What the hell is this? Are you fucking him?

34:30.947 --> 34:32.514
- Is that what this is?
- No, it isn't.

34:32.547 --> 34:33.911
Then what the hell is it, then?!

34:33.945 --> 34:35.510
If he doesn't get that
gun out of my fucking face,

34:35.543 --> 34:37.109
- I'm gonna fuckin' kill him.
- Stop it.

34:37.141 --> 34:38.815
You're gonna kill me? I don't think so.

34:38.848 --> 34:40.817
<i>- I don't give a fuck what you think.
- You show up at my house</i>

34:40.850 --> 34:42.521
- looking for my wife...
- You don't know what's going on,

34:42.554 --> 34:44.455
- so back off!
- I will blow your fucking head off!

34:44.487 --> 34:47.485
<i>- Last chance!
- He's Deva's father!</i>

35:14.120 --> 35:15.782
What...?

35:19.653 --> 35:22.451
What did you say?

35:23.893 --> 35:26.326
Gordon...

35:39.306 --> 35:41.674
Gordon...

35:45.615 --> 35:48.253
I will tell you everything.

35:50.286 --> 35:53.156
But right now I have to go.

35:54.895 --> 35:56.696
<i>Carrie: I have to go.</i>

35:57.760 --> 35:59.262
Why?

35:59.295 --> 36:01.994
Because I have to kill him.

36:02.027 --> 36:04.866
Or die trying.

36:04.899 --> 36:07.403
<i>[truck engine starts]</i>

36:15.214 --> 36:17.643
I meant what I said...
either he dies or we do.

36:17.676 --> 36:19.916
Nothing less.

36:21.687 --> 36:23.824
I couldn't agree more.

37:15.243 --> 37:18.544
<i>[heart monitor beeping]</i>

37:28.460 --> 37:32.160
<i>[beeping continues]</i>

38:06.798 --> 38:08.965
<i>[elevator bell rings]</i>

38:17.478 --> 38:21.110
[heart monitor beeping]

38:49.005 --> 38:50.676
[gunshots]

39:24.042 --> 39:27.184
[heart monitor beeping]

39:31.592 --> 39:34.660
[gasps]
Is that any way to greet an old friend?

39:34.693 --> 39:36.462
- Asshole.
- Can you move?

39:36.495 --> 39:39.230
- Barely.
- Come on, let's get you...

39:55.872 --> 39:57.945
[grunts]

39:59.250 --> 40:01.450
[gunshot]
Oh! Fuck!

40:02.386 --> 40:05.415
[nurses screaming]

40:37.979 --> 40:40.685
[gunshot]
Shots fired on the third floor.

40:40.718 --> 40:43.755
Request police backup. Drop your weapon!

41:13.053 --> 41:15.148
[grunting]

41:33.172 --> 41:35.170
[gunshot]

41:35.203 --> 41:37.337
[gasps]

41:44.949 --> 41:46.420
Help!

41:47.517 --> 41:50.219
Drop it! Drop the gun now.

41:50.252 --> 41:53.856
<i>Come out and drop the gun now.</i>

41:53.889 --> 41:55.595
<i>[speaking Ukrainian] Let her go!</i>

41:56.120 --> 41:58.120
<i>I'll shoot her in the head.</i>

42:04.331 --> 42:06.570
[nurse whimpering]

42:08.235 --> 42:10.107
<i>[speaking Ukrainian] I'm Rabbit's daughter.</i>

42:14.015 --> 42:15.837
<i>Are you sure he wants me dead?</i>

42:15.838 --> 42:17.600
<i>Stop talking.</i>

42:17.635 --> 42:20.340
<i>Because you had better be very sure
before you pull the trigger.</i>

42:21.117 --> 42:22.820
I'll kill her.

42:22.853 --> 42:24.156
[nurse screams]

42:24.189 --> 42:26.388
No, you won't.

42:30.197 --> 42:33.597
[whimpering]

42:35.799 --> 42:37.804
[panting]

42:37.837 --> 42:39.604
What took you so long?

42:39.637 --> 42:41.468
- He had a friend.
- Job: How about a little less talk

42:41.509 --> 42:43.509
and a little more getting
the fuck out of here?

42:43.542 --> 42:46.215
<i>[distant sirens wailing]
Shit.</i>

42:46.248 --> 42:48.417
Let's move.

42:50.218 --> 42:52.551
[chatter]

42:52.584 --> 42:55.317
I want men in all four stairwells.

42:55.358 --> 42:58.591
And be careful. The shooter
might still be in the building.

42:58.624 --> 43:01.064
You two, with me.

43:03.571 --> 43:05.631
I want you to head
down there, make a loop.

43:05.665 --> 43:08.332
We'll meet back up at ICU.

43:19.179 --> 43:21.810
Son of a bitch! Move, move, move!

43:24.852 --> 43:28.318
<i>[sirens wailing]
[helicopter blades whirring]</i>

43:33.386 --> 43:35.456
Lucas: So what the
hell were you thinking,

43:35.489 --> 43:37.592
trying to take him out on your own?

43:37.625 --> 43:40.499
I saw an opening and I took it.

43:40.533 --> 43:42.436
Would have finished him right there

43:42.469 --> 43:44.299
if it hadn't been for
that psycho priest.

43:44.332 --> 43:46.201
- Priest?
- Yulish.

43:46.234 --> 43:48.600
- What, you know him?
- He's my uncle.

43:48.633 --> 43:52.274
I never met him, but my
father used to talk about him.

43:52.307 --> 43:54.380
I always got the feeling
that he was scared of him.

43:54.413 --> 43:56.717
Are there any members of your family

43:56.750 --> 43:58.517
who aren't homicidal maniacs?

43:58.550 --> 44:01.085
<i>- We'll go in tomorrow.
- Job: I know the layout.</i>

44:01.118 --> 44:03.823
- I should come with you.
- You can't even stand, Job.

44:03.856 --> 44:07.832
It's just a concussion,
man. You get them every day.

44:07.865 --> 44:10.495
The inside of your head must
look like a Jackson Pollock.

44:10.528 --> 44:12.261
Can't have you slowing us down, okay?

44:15.040 --> 44:17.441
<i>Job: It's not exactly an arsenal.</i>

44:17.474 --> 44:20.611
Yeah, we had to leave
in a bit of a hurry.

44:20.645 --> 44:23.653
Hey, Pony still dealing
guns in these parts?

44:23.686 --> 44:26.684
Only dealing Pony's doing
is blow jobs in Sing Sing.

44:26.717 --> 44:29.021
<i>[gun clips clicking]</i>

44:30.222 --> 44:32.127
But you know who is still around?

44:33.865 --> 44:36.864
- You think?
- I'd have heard if someone took him out.

44:36.897 --> 44:38.165
Who?

44:38.198 --> 44:40.668
An old friend.

44:40.701 --> 44:45.007
He's using a very liberal
definition of the word "friend."

44:45.041 --> 44:48.714
- Think he'd remember me?
- The question is, do you want him to?

44:48.747 --> 44:51.516
[clicking]

44:51.549 --> 44:53.354
<i>[door closes]</i>

45:03.059 --> 45:05.465
Your men...?

45:05.498 --> 45:07.495
They are dead.

45:10.493 --> 45:12.502
Then they have come.

45:12.535 --> 45:14.735
Yes.

45:14.768 --> 45:17.840
I spent 15 years

45:17.873 --> 45:20.178
searching for my daughter.

45:20.211 --> 45:22.912
And now she hunts me.

45:28.016 --> 45:30.089
Tell me, Yulish.

45:31.154 --> 45:33.796
Do you really believe in God?

45:35.094 --> 45:37.731
I do, yes.

45:38.562 --> 45:41.167
<i>Rabbit: To me...</i>

45:41.200 --> 45:45.538
<i>God always felt like
something men made up</i>

45:45.571 --> 45:48.309
<i>to feel less alone.</i>

45:51.550 --> 45:53.317
<i>And now...</i>

45:55.748 --> 46:00.052
<i>I am more alone than I have ever been.</i>

46:02.423 --> 46:04.327
I don't trust you.

46:05.327 --> 46:07.892
I don't give a shit.

46:09.563 --> 46:12.467
<i>Rabbit: And instead
of wishing for God...</i>

46:13.732 --> 46:17.267
<i>I am praying...</i>

46:17.308 --> 46:19.740
<i>that He does not exist.</i>

46:20.771 --> 46:22.736
